nk\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}, {\"begin\": 290, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont des Arts\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not just because Nakamura is the world's most popular francophone performer and France's top-selling artiste; her work has garnered 7 billion in streams, and she has been hailed as the nation's biggest star since Piaf but with an even larger global reach.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather, it was a recognition of the evolution of French identity, culture and language.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 620, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8782044369914495, \"rank\": 0.13843782914286282, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nakamura was born in the West African nation of Mali - which was under French colonial rule for 70 years until 1960 - but grew up on a housing estate in abanlieueof the northern part of the greater Paris region, Seine-Saint-Denis.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 708, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9999400779856236, \"rank\": 2.849334394361439e-05, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}, {\"begin\": 731, \"end\": 751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_colonial_empi